Kevin Hourican -- Executive VP & President of CVS Pharmacy

Yeah, hi Bob, this is Kevin. I'll answer that question. So we're really pleased with our top line script growth, we're growing at two times the market. The vast majority of our script growth is coming from our clinical programs, which are intended to increase medication adherence to the patients that we serve. So those are existing customers of ours. And if we can keep them more adherent on taking their medications to keep them healthier and it also drives our business. As Eva mentioned, we also have strong strategic partnerships with third-party payers, and we're seeing growth with the major payers being able to shift share to us based on our preferred relationships. Those are the two primary drivers.

Robert Jones -- Goldman Sachs -- Analyst

